  <summary>This is the KWin port of the Glitch effect of the Burn-My-Windows GNOME Shell extension. &lt;a href="https://github.com/Schneegans/Burn-My-Windows#%EF%B8%8F-installation-kwin" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">You can find a list of all Burn-My-Windows effects which are currently available for KWin on GitHub.&lt;/a>&lt;br />
&lt;br />
&lt;strong>This effect requires at least KWin 5.25.0. Also, if the color picker widgets in the settings of any of the Burn-My-Windows effects do not work, you may have to install the package "libkf5widgetsaddons-dev" (Kubuntu, KDE Neon, etc) or "kwidgetsaddons-devel" (Fedora, OpenSuse, etc).&lt;/strong> If you encounter a bug or have a feature request, please open an issue on &lt;a href="https://github.com/Schneegans/Burn-My-Windows/issues" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">GitHub&lt;/a>!&lt;br />
&lt;br />
&lt;em>IMHO, there are many things which could be done to improve the KWin port of the extension. However, since I am not using KDE as a daily driver, I would appreciate it very much if someone volunteers to work on this port! I am happily receiving pull requests...&lt;/em>&lt;br />
&lt;br />
</summary>
